description:
Lost Legacy Reclaimedis a docudrama series about the early Christian Church in North Africa, its great leaders, teachers, and martyrs. Meet these faithful Christians from the first five centuries of church history who set a high standard for future generations by sacrificing for Jesus Christ during intense persecution from the Roman Empire and others. All of these stories take place in North Africa, then a part of the Roman Empire and today a region dominated by Islamic culture. Lost Legacy Reclaimed reveals the existence of a vibrant Christian community that predates the arrival of Islam. The four episodes cover Victor, The Scillitan Martyrs, Perpetua, and Tertullian.

Director: Denise Godwin
Starring: Miguel Maini, Enrique Selfa, Yasir Al-robahie, Maria Amparo Rerrero Marti, Perla Ahsen, Guillermo Lago Costas
